Governor Darius Ishaku of Taraba state has directed that all the civil servants from grade level 1 to 12 should stay away from work and remain at home for two weeks to enable the government to monitor the Covid  19. The governor’s directives is to effect from 25th March 2020. In a press statement sign by the governor’s press Secretary Hassan Mijiyawa said the governor has also approve a composition of a technical committee to ensure adequate control and sensitization of the state population on the outbreak of the COVID 19. “The technical committee is expected to expand stakeholders’ engagement and enhance sensitization across the state” “Similarly, those in essential services are exempted from the directives, the governor therefore urge the people of the state to effect social distance and observe good hygiene”